definition.value: Thioxanthene and its substitution derivatives.
A chlorprothixene in which the double bond adopts a (Z)-configuration.
A chlorprothixene in which the double bond adopts an (E)-configuration.
Any member of the class of phytoceramides in which the sphingoid base is specified as Delta(8)-phytosphingenine.
Compounds with the general structure R4B(-)M(+), where R are organyl groups and M(+) is a metal cation.
A salt R4B(-)M(+) where at least one of the R groups is an alkynyl group.
A compound R4B(-) where at least one of the R groups is an alkynyl group.
An antidepressant whose molecular structure consists of four ring-like structures in a T-shape.
Any member of a family of natural products which contains a 6H-isochromene-6,8(7H)-dione or an isoquinoline-6,8(2H,7H)-dione skeleton and its substituted derivatives thereof.

An  azaphilone that is 7,8-dihydro-6H-2-benzopyran substituted by a methyl group at position 7, oxo groups at positions 6 and 8, a propenyl group at position 3 and a (2,4-dihydroxy-6-methylbenzoyl)oxy group at position 7.
The (7R)-enantiomer of mitorubrin.
Compounds containing an aziridine ring that contains a quaternary nitrogen atom.
The (2S,3S)-diastereomer of 2-methylcitric acid.

A compound that specifically inhibits the reuptake of serotonin in the brain. This increases the serotonin concentration in the synaptic cleft which then activates serotonin receptors to a greater extent.
A bis(eta(5)-cyclopentadienyl)metal(II) having Ti(II) as the metal(II) species. The parent of the class of titanonocenes.
Compounds with structure RAs=AsR.
Arsonic acid and its As-hydrocarbyl derivatives.
Systems consisting of two or more molecular entities that are held together by their topology such that they cannot be separated without breaking bonds.
Mechanically-interlocked molecular entities where the constituent macrocyclic molecular entities are interlocked like links on a chain.

A system in which at least one macrocycle encloses another, rod-like molecule (shaft) having end groups too large to pass through the ring opening, and thus holds the rod-like molecule in position without covalent bonding.
Rotaxane consisting of a single shaft and single macrocycle.
Rotaxanes consisting of a single shaft and two macrocycles.
Rotaxanes consisting of a single shaft and three macrocycles.
A catenane consisting of two interlocked macrocycles.
A catenane consisting of three interlocked macrocycles.
Systems consisting of two or more molecular entities held together by non-covalent interactions.
A system consisting of a macrocycle non-covalently bound to a spindle molecule.
Pseudorotaxane consisting of a single macrocycle and a spindle molecule.
A racemate that is the butyl ester of fluazifop. It is used as a post-emergence herbicide for the control grass weeds in various broad-leaved crops.
Pseudorotaxane consisting of two macrocycles and a spindle molecule.
Pseudorotaxane consisting of three macrocycles and a spindle molecule.
The 2',3'-cyclic phosphate derivative of 7,8-dihydro-D-neopterin.
